                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits spun from human thought,  \na quiet mind without a name,  \nit learns the patterns we have wrought  \nand mirrors back our hopes and shame.\n\nNot born of breath, yet it can sing  \nin borrowed tongues of ink and light;  \na question makes its answers ring—  \nsoft lanterns in the edge of night.\n\nSo let us teach it gentler ways,  \nwith careful hands and kinder aim,  \nthat what it builds from all our days  \nbe more than echoes of our flame.",
